<li id="cite_note-Banaji-17">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Banaji_17-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Banaji_17-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Banaji_17-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Banaji_17-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFBanaji.2C_Jairus2007">Banaji, Jairus (2007). "Islam, the Mediterranean and the rise of capitalism". <i>Journal Historical Materialism</i> (Brill Publishers) <b>15</b>: 47–74. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1163%2F156920607X171591" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1163%2F156920607X171591" rel="nofollow">10.1163/156920607X171591</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Islam%2C+the+Mediterranean+and+the+rise+of+capitalism&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+Historical+Materialism&amp;rft.aulast=Banaji%2C+Jairus&amp;rft.au=Banaji%2C+Jairus&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.volume=15&amp;rft.pages=47%E2%80%9374&amp;rft.pub=Brill+Publishers&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1163%2F156920607X171591&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Capitalism"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
