<li id="cite_note-state_capitalism-93"><b><a href="#cite_ref-state_capitalism_93-0" title="">^</a></b> Early proponents of the term "state capitalism" include, for example, <a href="/wiki/Tony_Cliff" title="Tony Cliff">Tony Cliff</a>, <a href="/wiki/Raya_Dunayevskaya" title="Raya Dunayevskaya">Raya Dunayevskaya</a>, <a href="/wiki/CLR_James" title="CLR James" class="mw-redirect">CLR James</a> and <a href="/wiki/Paul_Mattick" title="Paul Mattick">Paul Mattick</a>. <a href="/wiki/Ernest_Mandel" title="Ernest Mandel">Ernest Mandel</a> has been a particularly prominent advocate of the analysis of post-WWII conditions as <a href="/wiki/State_capitalism" title="State capitalism">state capitalism</a>. (See, for example, Mandel's <i>The Theory of “State Capitalism”</i>.<cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFErnest_Mandel1951-06-01">Ernest Mandel (1951-06-01). <a href="http://web.archive.org/web/20061002030657/http://www.ernestmandel.org/en/works/txt/FI/theory_of_statecapitalism.htm" class="external text" title="http://web.archive.org/web/20061002030657/http://www.ernestmandel.org/en/works/txt/FI/theory_of_statecapitalism.htm" rel="nofollow">"The Theory of “State Capitalism”"</a>. Archived from <a href="http://www.ernestmandel.org/en/works/txt/FI/theory_of_statecapitalism.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.ernestmandel.org/en/works/txt/FI/theory_of_statecapitalism.htm" rel="nofollow">the original</a> on 2006-10-02<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://web.archive.org/web/20061002030657/http://www.ernestmandel.org/en/works/txt/FI/theory_of_statecapitalism.htm" class="external free" title="http://web.archive.org/web/20061002030657/http://www.ernestmandel.org/en/works/txt/FI/theory_of_statecapitalism.htm" rel="nofollow">http://web.archive.org/web/20061002030657/http://www.ernestmandel.org/en/works/txt/FI/theory_of_statecapitalism.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-02-26</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_v